subject: RE: [junit] TestCase Dependency Hierarchy
msgSnippet: ... Tsk.  Aristotle said this way before Russell.  In more than one place Aristotle stated (to paraphrase in English): From a false premise, anything
messageBody:
>> -----Original Message-----
>> Actually, Bertrand Russell contended that
>> from an incorrect hypothesis any conclusion
>> can be proven, which has corrolary that all
>> conclusions are therefore invalid.

Tsk. Aristotle said this way before Russell. In more than one place Aristotle stated (to paraphrase in English): "From a false premise, anything follows." He was talking about syllogistic logic, which he invented.

Nowadays we just say "garbage in; garbage out."

Scott Stirling
Framingham, MA
